"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The roc_curve function is being used incorrectly for multiclass classification. The y_test should be the binary labels for each class, but in this case, it's the original multiclass labels. Also, y_score should be the predicted probabilities for each class, but it's being passed as is. We need to use the y_onehot_test instead of y_test and also need to pass the predicted probabilities for each class separately.\",\n  \"patch\": \"28,29c28,29\\n< for i in range(n_classes):\\n<     fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_test, y_score, pos_label=i)\\n---\\n> for i in range(n_classes):\\n>     fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i])\\n\"\n}"